<sn><md>#### Geographical Location

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
The ancient Greek civilization `developed around the Mediterranean Sea`. Due to geographical and cultural reasons, two cultural names are associated with Greek civilization: one is **‘Hellenic’** and the other is **‘Hellenistic’**.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://c8.alamy.com/comp/3D7664P/ancient-greek-colonies-and-parent-cities-history-map-greek-colonization-during-the-archaic-period-750-to-550-bc-across-mediterranean-and-black-sea-3D7664P.jpg)
:::
:::

**Greece** is known as the country of `Hellenic` civilization. The culture that developed from the beginning in Athens, the main city of Greece, is called `Hellenic culture`. The `Greek peninsula` was the main center of this culture. The Hellenic civilization `lasted until 337 BC`.

During this time, a new culture was born in `Alexandria of Egypt` through the ++blending of Greek and non-Greek cultures++. In history, this culture is known as `Hellenistic culture`.

</md></sn><sn><md>#### Religion

The Greeks believed in `polytheism`. The `chief god` of the Greeks was ++Zeus++. Gods such as `Apollo` and goddess `Athena` were also highly important. The Greeks believed that the gods `lived at` the summit of ++Mount Olympus++ in northern Greece.

**Greek Gods and Goddesses: Names and Descriptions**

| Name of Greek God/Goddess | Description                                          |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| **Aphrodite**             | Goddess of `love, romance, and beauty`                 |
| **Artemis**               | Goddess of `hunting, forests, fertility, and the moon` |
| **Demeter**               | Goddess of `agriculture`                               |
| **Athena**                | Goddess of `wisdom` (++daughter of Zeus++)                 |
| **Hera**                  | Goddess of `marriage and family` (++wife of Zeus++)        |
| **Zeus**                  | `King` of the gods                                     |
| **Apollo**                | God of the `sun, light, medicine, and music`           |
| **Ares**                  | God of `war`                                           |
| **Hermes**                | God of `commerce` (++Roman name: Mercury++)                |

